│ Let me check how the tree is built for the icmp instructions.                                                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ In the reproducer, we have multiple icmp instructions that are candidates for vectorization. The SLP vectorizer will try to build a tree with these icmp instructions as the root.        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ For each icmp instruction, it will look at its operands:                                                                                                                                  │
│ - Operand 1: `and i32 (zext i16 X to i32), 0`                                                                                                                                             │
│ - Operand 2: `zext i16 Y to i32`                                                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ The vectorizer will try to vectorize these operands as well.                                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ For operand 2 (the zext instructions), it will create a tree entry for the zext instructions. The type for this tree entry should be i32 (the result type of zext).                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ For operand 1 (the and instructions), it will create a tree entry for the and instructions, with type i32.                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ So when the icmp instructions are vectorized, their operands should be i32 vectors.                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ The only way we get i16 is if the vectorizer is looking through the zext cast when building the tree.                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ Looking at the tree building code, there might be other places where casts are looked through.                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ But the root cause analysis specifically points to the `CreateInsertElement` lambda, so I think that's the right place to fix.                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ Perhaps the issue is that my fix is not complete. Let me look at the code again.                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ In the original code:                                                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                    │
│ Value *Scalar = V;                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ if (Scalar->getType() != Ty) {                                                                                                                                                            │
│   assert(Scalar->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy() &&                                                                                                                                       │
